reviews.text:
Reviewed as part of the Mixer's Club. I am not giving this a star rating since I don't feel like it is a recipe I would have mixed up on my own since I do not typically like cherry vapes. They all unfortunately taste medicinal to me. However, if you enjoy cherry vapes, this may be a fantastic recipe for you to try out! Every other aspect of it was really really good.&#xD;
&#xD;
Just from smell, I am guessing the pink is strawberry. Definitely something else in there, but I cannot place it on smell alone.&#xD;
&#xD;
Whoa, based off of smell, this is not what I was expecting at all. I have now changed my mind from strawberry to cherry. I think I am sensitive to the medicinal off-notes of cherries because all of my medicine as a child was cherry flavored, but this one is extremely minor and not offensive at all. Definitely some sort of custard/pudding/cream mixture in here, but I cannot place any of the individual flavors. Whatever it is, t is definitely tasty and thick. I am also getting some vanilla in the background, but most custards and pudding seem to be vanilla flavored by default.&#xD;
&#xD;
After looking at the recipe, I am very confused. I get the strawberry off the smell, but only taste the cherry when actually vaping. I’m actually really embarrassed that I can’t taste any of the CAP Sweet Guava either since it is one of my favorite flavors. However, I normally use it a bit higher cus I like the “funkiness” that it brings. I think using INW Custard to thicken FLV Vanilla Pudding up was a smart move and works very well. The vanilla is nice as well, so I’m glad that little bit of FLV Smooth Vanilla was added to help out FLV Vanilla Pudding.  &#xD;
&#xD;
Overall, I really enjoyed the recipe, but I personally didn’t get any strawberry or Sweet Guava. That is more than likely just me though since I’m very sensitive to the cherry. &#xD;
